        "theme":  "Strategy",
        "summary":  "CIOs are restructuring their organizations to simultaneously accelerate AI adoption and manage risk, often by separating innovation teams from compliance functions. Industry leaders emphasize that effective data governance, clear business objectives, and formal risk management frameworks are prerequisites for scaling AI responsibly. The article examines how top technology executives are designing operating models that enable speed without sacrificing security or control.",
        "execSummary":  "The core challenge for enterprise technology leaders is no longer whether to adopt AI but how to scale it without creating unmanageable risk exposure. CIOs interviewed for this piece are responding by building separate innovation and compliance structures, ensuring neither function bottlenecks the other. For customer-support and operations leaders, the takeaway is structural: AI governance cannot live in a single team ΓÇö it must be distributed across the organization with clear accountability. The caveat is that separating innovation from compliance requires strong cross-functional communication or the two functions will pull strategy in opposite directions.",
