        "summary":  "Anthropic launched Claude Tag, a Slack-based tool that enables teams to collaborate with a shared AI assistant retaining context across conversations and channels. The offering positions AI as a shared team resource rather than an individual productivity tool, functioning as a form of persistent organizational memory. CIOs will need new governance frameworks and ROI metrics adapted to collaborative rather than individual AI usage.",
        "execSummary":  "Claude Tag signals a meaningful architectural shift in enterprise AI: from solo productivity tools to shared team agents embedded in communication platforms. For customer-support and operations leaders, this opens a path to AI systems that accumulate institutional context across shifts and teams ΓÇö a meaningful improvement over stateless chatbots. Anthropic\u0027s move also introduces new governance complexity, since shared AI memory creates questions about data access, conversation privacy, and accountability for AI-generated decisions. Enterprise buyers should evaluate not just the capability but the controls Anthropic provides over what the agent retains and who can see it.",
