        "summary":  "A Protiviti survey of more than 850 global executives reveals a significant confidence gap: 61% of CIOs believe AI drives revenue growth, while fewer than one-third of CEOs and board members share that view. The divergence indicates that AI maturity levels and alignment on success metrics are critical factors in whether organizations realize tangible outcomes from AI investments. The disconnect between technology and business leadership creates organizational friction that slows AI strategy execution.",
        "execSummary":  "The AI value gap is not primarily a technology problem ΓÇö it is a communication and alignment problem between technology leaders and the C-suite. Protiviti\u0027s data shows CIOs and CEOs are operating with fundamentally different mental models of what AI is delivering, which means AI strategy decisions are being made without a shared factual baseline. For enterprise leaders, this argues for establishing shared, board-visible AI value metrics before expanding AI investments ΓÇö not after. The watch item is that this perception gap tends to widen as AI deployments grow more complex, making early alignment on measurement frameworks critical to sustaining executive support.",
