        "summary":  "As AI systems advance, enterprises face a critical bottleneck in accessing fresh, real-time web data at scale, with traditional static training data insufficient for modern business needs like market tracking and pricing intelligence. A new category of web data infrastructure is emerging to enable AI models to retrieve current, contextually relevant information while maintaining regulatory compliance. This infrastructure layer addresses hallucination reduction through high-quality, current data feeds and supports retrieval-augmented generation at enterprise scale.",
        "execSummary":  "Enterprise AI deployments are increasingly constrained not by model capability but by data freshness ΓÇö a problem that static training data cannot solve. The article describes an emerging infrastructure category designed to give AI systems real-time web access, which directly addresses the accuracy and reliability gaps that undermine enterprise trust in AI outputs. For customer-support and operations leaders, this has practical implications: AI systems grounded in current data perform more reliably on pricing, policy, and product queries than those relying on stale training data. The caveat is that this article reads as a vendor-framed thought-leadership piece; buyers should independently evaluate whether the infrastructure claims hold at their specific data volumes and compliance requirements.",
