        "theme":  "Platforms",
        "summary":  "IBM has developed a prototype chip featuring approximately 100 billion transistors stacked vertically in two layers, achieving double the density of its 2021 technology in a nanostack architecture. The design addresses the physical limits of transistor miniaturization by building vertically rather than shrinking further, delivering up to 50% more compute performance and 70% greater energy efficiency. Industry analysts suggest this innovation could extend the semiconductor roadmap by 10-15 years, with data center applications as the primary beneficiary.",
